  "prompt": "Why do men get angry when their girlfriend/ wife ends the relationship when they caused the breakup?",
  "response": "There can be several psychological and emotional reasons for this reaction:\n\n1. Lack of accountability\n- They often fail to recognize their own role in causing the breakup\n- Prefer to see themselves as the victim\n- Blame the partner for leaving instead of examining their own behavior\n\n2. Ego protection\n- Feeling rejected hurts their pride\n- Cannot handle being \"dumped\" first\n- Want to maintain a sense of control\n\n3. Emotional immaturity\n- Struggle with processing complex emotions\n- Unable to accept responsibility for their actions\n- Defensive mechanism to avoid dealing with personal failures\n\n4. Possessiveness\n- View partner as a possession\n- Feel entitled to the relationship\n- Cannot accept losing \"control\" over the relationship\n\n5. Unresolved emotional issues\n- May have deep-seated insecurities\n- Past trauma or attachment issues\n- Difficulty accepting loss\n\n6. Cognitive dissonance\n- Their perception of events differs from reality\n- Cannot reconcile their actions with the relationship's end\n- Struggle to accept their own role in the breakup\n\n7. Emotional manipulation\n- Some use anger as a tool to guilt or control their partner\n- Want to make the partner feel bad or reconsider leaving\n\nThese reactions stem from complex emotional and psychological factors and aren't universal to all men.",
